# Byte-exact test fixtures.
#
# tests/fixtures/parity/ holds .dgt files whose exact bytes ARE the test.
# test-dgt-cross-platform.R md5s them raw via .byte_signature(). With
# core.autocrlf=true on Windows (the default for many installs), git would
# rewrite the macOS-authored LF fixture to CRLF on checkout and silently
# destroy the evidence the test exists to check.
#
# -text disables all end-of-line conversion while keeping the files diffable.
*.dgt   -text
*.DGT   -text

# Session data written by GUImorphWeb. Same reasoning: the writer's exact
# output is what round-trip tests compare.
*.ply   -text
*.pts   -text
